README file for KSTR (22 Jan 2008)

Run KSTR as:

 ./source/kstr < JOBNAM.dat

Input file: JOBNAM.dat 

Sample files: 
             fcc.dat            (face centered cubic)
             bco0-5.dat         (body centered orthorombic, 
                                 distorted fcc e=0.00-0.05 for C44)
             fco0-5.dat         (face centered orthorombic, 
                                 distorted fcc e=0.00-0.05 for (C11-C12)/2))
             bcc.dat            (body centered cubic)
             Bco0-5.dat         (body centered orthorombic, 
                                 distorted bcc e=0.00-0.05 for (C11-C12)/2))
             Fco0-5.dat         (face centered orthorombic, 
                                 distorted bcc e=0.00-0.05 for C44)
             hcp.dat            (hexagonal close packed c/a=1.63299316)
             hcpm0-5.dat        (monoclinic with basis,
                                 distorted hcp  e=0.00-0.05 for C44, c/a=1.603)
             hcpo0-5.dat        (basis centered orthorombic with basis,
                                 distorted hcp  e=0.00-0.05 for C66, c/a=1.603)

Input-output:

 JOBNAM     -name for the job, slope matrix file
 DIR001     -location for the slope matrix file: JOBNAM.tfh
 DIR006     -location for the printout: JOBNAM.prn

parameter comment                                      recommended

  MSGL   -controls the printout on the screen               1
  MODE   -bulk (B) or surface (S) mode                      B
  STORE  -store (Y) or not (N) the slope matrix             Y (always)
  HIGH   -calculate (Y) or not (N) the higers               Y (always)
  NL     -number of orbitals included (1,2,...,5)         
  NLH    -number of highers included  (NLH>NL)              9 (or 11)
  NLW    -Watson sphere for positive energies               9
  NDER   -number of energy derivatives of the slope matrix  6 (at least 4)
  ITRANS -screening matrix                                  3 (always)
  NPRN   -printout in JOBNAM.prn
  (K*W)^2-center of Taylor expansion                        0.0
         -in the case of wide bands a second set of slope
          matrix has to be generated for a negative (K*W)^2~ -20.0
  DMAX   -radius of the cluster, its value depends on the
          crystal and on the screening
         -when calculating energy versus distortion (e.g., E(c/a)), DMAX
          should be modified as the number of sites in the cluster
          should remain constant
  RWATS  -the radius of the Watson sphere is DMAX+RWATS     0.1
  NQ3    -number of atoms in the unit cell
  LAT    -lattice:
          1      Simple cubic                                
          2      Face centred cubic                          
          3      Body centred cubic                          
          4      Hexagonal close packed                      
          5      Simple tetragonal                           
          6      Body centred tetragonal                     
          7      Trigonal                                    
          8      Simple orthorombic                          
          9      Base centred orthorombic                    
         10      Body centred orthorombic                    
         11      Face centred orthorombic                    
         12      Simple monoclinic                           
         13      Base centred monoclinic                     
         14      Simple triclinic                            
  IPRIM  -default (1) or special (0) setup of the primitive
          vectors for IPRIM=1 the 10-12th lines has to be 
          changed to a single line:
ALPHA....=    90.000 BETA....=    90.000 GAMMA...=    90.000
          where ALPHA,BETA,GAMMA are the angles formed by
          A-C, C-A, A-B primitive vectors, respectively
  NGHBP  -number of unit cells for generating the cluster   13
  NQR2                                                       0
  A,B,C  -lattice parameters
  BSX,Y,Z-primitive vectors units of A (needed only for IPRIM=0)
  QX,Y,Z -basis vactors in units of A
  a/w    -hard sphere radii in units of Wigner-Seitz radii   0.70 (or smaller)
  LAMDA  -constants for the Ewald sum of the Madelung matrix
  AMAX
  BMAX
